Characters of uncertain polarity shared with whatcheeriids (
Warren & Turner, 2004
):

Numerous isolated tetrapod bones have been recovered from the Blue Beach locality at Horton Bluff (both names are used interchangeably to refer to this locality) in Nova Scotia (
Anderson et al. , 2015
). Blue Beach is important because it, and the similarly aged Ballagan Formation in Britain, provide the currently known suite of Tournaisian tetrapods ( Clack & Finney, 2005 ;
Smithson et al. , 2012
;
Clack et al ., 2016
, 2019a ;
Chen et al. , 2018
;
Otoo et al. , 2018
; Smithson & Clack, 2018 ;
Lennie et al. , 2020
).
